I'll handle the transformation error by first verifying the data format and then retrying the transformation with explicit format specification.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

I'll attempt to convert the input data to XML format before retrying the transformation, as the transformer expects XML input.

<tool_call>file_operations_converter
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "xml",
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now that we've successfully converted the data to XML format, I'll retry the transformation step with the converted data.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "source": "data/input.xml",
  "options": {
    "format": "xml"
  }
}
</tool_call>

            I'll try using the integration_mapper tool as an alternative for the transformation step, since the data_processing_transformer keeps failing.

<tool_call>integration_mapper
{
  "input_format": "xml",
  "output_format": "json",
  "source": "data/input.xml",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now that we've successfully transformed the data, I'll proceed with the filtering step using the data_processing_filter tool.

